:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/getNode(path:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" and similar functions. It can reference a node, a resource within a node, or a property of a node or resource. For example, ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"Path2D\/PathFollow2D\/Sprite2D:texture:size\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" would refer to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"size"},{"type":"text","text":" property of the "},{"code":"texture","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" resource on the node named ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"Sprite2D\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which is a child of the other named nodes in the path."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You will usually just pass a string to ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/getNode(path:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and it will be automatically converted, but you may occasionally want to parse a path ahead of time with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/NodePath","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or the literal syntax "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"^\"path\""},{"type":"text","text":". Exporting a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/NodePath"},{"text":" variable will give you a node selection widget in the properties panel of the editor, which can often be useful.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/NodePath","type":"reference"},{"text":" is composed of a list of slash-separated node names (like a filesystem path) and an optional colon-separated list of “subnames” which can be resources or properties.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some examples of NodePaths include the following:","type":"text"}]},{"inl